KCTU calls general strike 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 6 (KCNA) -- The South Korean Confederation of Trade Unions went on a general strike on July 5 in demand of a stop to the suppression of workers and restructuring, etc., according to Seoul-based Radio No. 1.
 The KCTU clarified that the general strike is participated in by at least 100,000 unionists of over 80 workshops across South Korea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Earlier on July 4, Tan Pyong Ho, chairman of the KCTU, called a press conference at Myongdong cathedral where a hunger-strike is under way under the strict watch of police. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the conference he declared that the organization would go on a general strike from July 5 as scheduled. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general strike would be participated in mainly by those under the federation of metal industrial workers unions and the federation of chemical fibre industrial workers unions, he said, adding: More than 10,000 of over 20 workshops would boycot their work by holding general meetings, the federation of democratic taxi drivers' unions by discontinuing taxi service for 6 hours while teachers of the "national teachers' union" would join in the strike by leaving work early. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization declared its plan to open big meetings with the attendance of more than 70,000 people in over 20 places including Jongmyo Park in Seoul on July 5 and rallies in 16 localities on July 6 and general meetings of unionists and demonstrations in 17 regions on July 7.

Reunification festival of Koreans in Americas held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 6 (KCNA) -- A reunification festival of Koreans in Americas for the implementation of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration was held in Washington D.C. on June 16. 
 At the festival Ri Haeng U, president of the American union for independence, democracy and reunification, made an opening address, which was followed by speeches and congratulatory speeches of representatives from all walks of life. Noting that it is the historic duty for all members of the nation to implement the north-south joint declaration, the speakers called on the compatriots in Americas to pool efforts for reconciliation, cooperation, independence and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An appeal to the compatriots in Americas was adopted at the festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal said that the joint declaration promises the future of a reunified prosperous country where the 70 million fellow countrymen will live in harmony. It called upon the compatriots in Americas to positively solidarize with the national movement for the implementation of the declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A statement to the U.S. government was made public at the festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said: the U.S. government should support and respect the north-south joint declaration, opt for normalizing relations with the DPRK at an early date, promote dialogue with the DPRK for the sincere implementation of the DPRK-U.S. joint communique and help toward peace on the Korean peninsula.

Withdrawal of U.S. forces from S. Korea urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 6 (KCNA) -- The Peruvian committee for supporting the independent and peaceful reunification of Korea issued a statement on June 25 on the occasion of a month of international solidarity with the Korean people.
 The statement said that the victory in the fatherland liberation war half a century ago was a historic event in which the Korean people repulsed the aggression of the imperialist allied forces and defended their sovereignty and dignity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It strongly demanded that the U.S. immediately and unconditionally withdraw its military personnel and equipment from South Korea before it sustains a defeat again in korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, solidarity meetings were held in Guinea, Poland and Austria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the meetings speakers noted that the brilliant victory of the Korean people and people's army in the last Korean War is the fruition of President Kim Il Sung's outstanding Juche-based war method and wise leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should not raise a hue and cry about "missile threat" from North Korea but drop its hostile policy towards the DPRK and pull its troops out of South Korea at an early date, they said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They extended firm solidarity to the Korean people in their struggle for the independent and peaceful reunification of the country.

Anniversary of Korean revolutionary army observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 6 (KCNA) -- Today marks the 71st anniversary of the creation of the Korean revolutionary army by general Kim Il Sung. He created the Korean revolutionary army, the first armed contingent of Korean communists and a political and para-military organization for preparing an anti-Japanese armed struggle. 
 At an inaugural ceremony he underscored the need to build the hardcore force for the armed struggle through positive political and military activities and secure weapons necessary for the armed struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called for making thoroughgoing preparations for the organized anti-Japanese armed struggle by accumulating military experience and firmly uniting broad popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under his wise leadership the KRA rapidly gained in scope and strength and core elements were built up to found standing revolutionary armed forces. activities were conducted in various places to obtain weapons in order to equip the kra soldiers with them. After organizing the KRA he formed various armed groups to dispatch them to various regions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The armed groups conducted bold activities in different places. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A mass foundation for the armed struggle expanded and rich experience was accumulated and a noble revolutionary spirit created to found revolutionary armed forces thanks to vigorous political and military activities of the KRA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On this basis he founded the anti-Japanese people's guerrilla army on April 25, Juche 21 (1932), declaring an all-out war against the Japanese imperialists.

Kim Jong Il sends message of sympathy to Russian President
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 6 (KCNA)-Leader Kim Jong Il sent a message of sympathy to Russian President Vladimir Vladimirovich Putin today.
The message reads: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Upon hearing a very sad news that all the crew and passengers of a russian airliner were killed in its crash in Russia on July 3, I express deep sorrow to you and, through you, to the Russian people and the bereaved families of the deceased. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
I sincerely hope that you will master your sorrow and register a success in your responsible work for the prosperity and peace of the Russian people
